{"schema_version":"1","crate":"utilada_lzma","version":"2.9.0","id":"7b0b9890d39f084f","name":"Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma","qualified_name":"Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"src/util-log-appenders-rolling_files-lzma.ads","line":35,"column":9},"code":"package Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma","documentation":{"description":"=== LZMA Rolling file appender ===\nThe `LzmaRollingFile` appender is similar to the `RollingFile` appender\nbut it compresses the file using LZMA when rotation occurs.\nTo use it, it is necessary to add `utilada_lzma` GNAT project and\ndeclare `LzmaRollingFile` factory by using:\n\n\n  with Util.Log.Appenders.Factories;\n  with Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma;\n  ...\n  package Lzma_Rolling_Factory is\n     new Util.Log.Appenders.Factories\n       (Name   => \"LzmaRollingFile\",\n        Create => Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma.Create'Access)\n          with Unreferenced;\n\nThen, you can use the `LzmaRollingFile` appender by using the same\ndefinitions as in the *Rolling file appender* but replacing `RollingFile`\nby the name you have defined, and by adding a `.xz` extension, for example:\n\n  log4j.appender.applogger=RollingFile\n  log4j.appender.applogger.filePattern=logs/debug-%d{YYYY-MM}/debug-%{dd}-%i.log.xz"},"tagged_types":[{"id":"3719d4dd0b240532","name":"File_Appender","qualified_name":"Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma.File_Appender","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"src/util-log-appenders-rolling_files-lzma.ads","line":40,"column":9},"code":"type File_Appender (Length    : Positive;\n                    Formatter : Formatter_Access) is new Appender with private;","parent_type":{"qualified_name":"Util.Log.Appenders.Appender","id":"0256e02d71b5d41f","unit":"util-log-appenders"},"dispatching_overridden":[{"qualified_name":"Util.Log.Appenders.Rolling_Files.Lzma.Append","id":"cec7bbb11b31eccc","unit":"util-log-appenders-rolling_files-lzma"},{"qualifi